eviation observed between the coretop temperature signal, as estimated by UK\&\#8242; 37, and AnnO. Our results indicate that the deviation can best be explained if seasonality in production and/or thermocline production as well as differential degradation of 37:3 and 37:2 alkenones both affect the sedimentary alkenone signal.},
