ual trends$\backslash$n(p \&lt; 0.10) of about +1 K decade\&\#8722;1 are found at three stations$\backslash$nin interior and coastal East Antarctica since 1992. The subtle shift$\backslash$ntoward warming during the past 15 years raises the question of whether$\backslash$nthe recent trends are linked more closely to anthropogenic influences$\backslash$nor multidecadal variability.},
